The good news for all concerned in Monaco was that it had stopped raining.

Arsene Wenger had raised fears on the eve of the game and as the downpour continued into the night the Arsenal manager wasn't the only one casting anxious glances skywards.

This is a big day for the new AS Monaco and they do not want it washed out.

